<div id="review_595826235" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/595826235" />
    <a title="Weina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13804707-weina"><img alt="Weina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509388902p2/13804707.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/595826235?book_show_action=true">Apr 20, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Weina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Weina" href="/user/show/13804707-weina">Weina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer595826235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10506959166785121051">I&apos;m so glad I read this book! Growing up in China, I&apos;ve heard so many brutal tales about Cixi that I was almost ready to resist her even before I started reading. But how amazing it is to see Anchee Min tell the story. She got me on page one. The narrative is subtle, the historical details rich, and I also like the way she injects the older Cixi&apos;s retrospection in the story.</span>
  <span id="freeText10506959166785121051" style="display:none">I'm so glad I read this book! Growing up in China, I've heard so many brutal tales about Cixi that I was almost ready to resist her even before I started reading. But how amazing it is to see Anchee Min tell the story. She got me on page one. The narrative is subtle, the historical details rich, and I also like the way she injects the older Cixi's retrospection in the story.</span>
