<div id="review_2082252564" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2082252564" />
    <a title="Kathryn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6504379-kathryn"><img alt="Kathryn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590065910p2/6504379.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2082252564?book_show_action=true">May 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathryn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathryn" href="/user/show/6504379-kathryn">Kathryn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6504379-kathryn?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6504379-kathryn?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6504379-kathryn?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6504379-kathryn?shelf=asian">asian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6504379-kathryn?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2082252564" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12125740145461423365">4.5 stars. <br/><br/>I&apos;m a lover of Asian fiction and Asian historical-fiction. I&apos;ve always been fascinated by Asia, as a whole, it&apos;s history, different traditions, ways of life, etc. Asian fiction and Asian historical-fiction are possibly my favorite genres to read. <br/><br/>This Asian historical-fiction is about the woman who would become China&apos;s last empress, Orchid. When you meet her, she comes from a poor Manchu family, and this follows her life into how she became the most powerful woman in China&apos;s history. </span>
  <span id="freeText12125740145461423365" style="display:none">4.5 stars. <br /><br />I'm a lover of Asian fiction and Asian historical-fiction. I've always been fascinated by Asia, as a whole, it's history, different traditions, ways of life, etc. Asian fiction and Asian historical-fiction are possibly my favorite genres to read. <br /><br />This Asian historical-fiction is about the woman who would become China's last empress, Orchid. When you meet her, she comes from a poor Manchu family, and this follows her life into how she became the most powerful woman in China's history. <br /><br />Not only was Orchid's life and character interesting, but learning about all of the customs and traditions of Ancient China were also equally fascinating. Learning how women became the wives of the Emperor was interesting. This is a very political novel, and probably not in the way you'd expect. You learn of the politics behind choosing wives, but also the politics the wives have to take part in for their own survival. There is also politics because of what was going on with China at the time, Europe, Russia, etc. and opium and shipping ports. <br /><br />I think Anchee Min did such a great job taking the reader through Orchid's life, explaining history, customs, traditions, and why some things had to be done as they were. Min also did a great job with Orchid's voice, her growth of character, and I think because of the novel being told from her perspective, we see why she becomes who she becomes in the end. <br /><br />The first couple of pages were a little difficult for me to get into, and some of it could have just been my mindset at the time. However, around ten pages in, I began to not be able to put the novel down because it was so engrossing. I also think the way Anchee Min ends the novel, and the point in Orchid's life where this first book ends, was also perfect timing. <br /><br />I really enjoyed this book, and I'm immediately picking up the second part of this duology, which is <i>The Last Empress</i>. I'm so looking forward to seeing how Orchid's story ends. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12125740145461423365" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


